    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Photomechanical prints produced by photolithography in which the printing plate is prepared using a bichromate process, gelatin, and greasy ink, which is held in the characteristic wormlike patterns of cracks.</Note_Text>
